
-- Block 4: Bloodborne Pathogens and Cleaning
UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Bloodborne pathogens travel through blood and bodily fluids. You cannot see them. You cannot smell them. But they are there, and they can enter the body through cuts, broken skin, or mucous membranes. This is not something to fear. It is something to respect. Every time you put on gloves, every time you follow exposure protocols, you are honoring the seriousness of what lives inside the human body. Your precautions are not paranoia. They are professionalism at the highest level.',
  affirmation = 'I respect what I cannot see. I protect myself and my clients with every precaution I take. My safety practices are not optional. They are who I am.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Bloodborne Pathogens';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'The liver is the body''s filter. Everything passes through it. Hepatitis is a virus that attacks that filter directly, causing inflammation and damage to one of the most important organs you have. Certain forms of hepatitis spread through infected blood and bodily fluids, which means your salon procedures are part of the line of defense. You do not need to be a doctor to understand why this matters. You need to be a professional who takes infection control seriously enough to follow every protocol without exception.',
  affirmation = 'I understand the weight of what I am protecting against. I follow every protocol not because someone is watching, but because my clients deserve that standard of care.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Hepatitis';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'HIV attacks the immune system itself. It weakens the body''s ability to fight off other infections and diseases by targeting the very cells designed to protect you. It spreads through blood and certain bodily fluids. While it cannot survive long outside the human body, the consequences of exposure are serious. This is why universal precautions exist. You treat every situation with the same level of care, not because you assume the worst about anyone, but because you hold yourself to the highest standard of protection.',
  affirmation = 'I do not make assumptions about who is safe and who is not. I treat every interaction with the same level of care. That consistency is my integrity.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'HIV';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Cleaning is where everything starts. Before you disinfect, before you sanitize, you clean. You remove the dirt, the debris, the visible material with soap and water. It is not glamorous, but it is essential. Disinfectants cannot do their job on a dirty surface. Think of cleaning as laying the foundation. You would never build a house on uneven ground. You would never disinfect a tool covered in product buildup. The first step is always the first step for a reason.',
  affirmation = 'I never skip the foundation. I clean first because I understand that every step in my process matters. I build my practice on solid ground.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Cleaning';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Sanitation is about bringing the risk down to a safe level. You are not eliminating every single microorganism. You are reducing them to a point where they can no longer cause harm. Think of it like turning down the volume on something dangerous until it is no longer a threat. In a shared environment where multiple clients sit in your chair every day, sanitation is what keeps the space safe between services. It is quiet, consistent work that protects everyone.',
  affirmation = 'I reduce risk with every action I take. I do not need to eliminate everything to be effective. I bring the danger down to a level where my clients are safe, and I do it every single time.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Sanitation';

-- Block 5: Disinfection and Safety
UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Disinfection goes deeper than cleaning. Cleaning removes what you can see. Disinfection destroys what you cannot. Chemical products designed to eliminate most harmful microorganisms on nonporous surfaces are what stand between your client and the invisible threats living on your tools. This is not an extra step. This is the step that separates a professional from someone who just goes through the motions. When you disinfect properly, you are saying I take this seriously.',
  affirmation = 'I go beyond the surface. I destroy what hides beneath it. My disinfection practice is not a task I complete. It is a standard I uphold.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Disinfection';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Sterilization is the highest level. It destroys everything, bacteria, viruses, fungi, and even the toughest spores. Nothing survives sterilization. It is the gold standard of decontamination, typically reserved for medical settings. But knowing where it sits in the hierarchy matters. You need to understand that cleaning, sanitation, disinfection, and sterilization are not the same thing. Each one builds on the last. And sterilization sits at the very top as the complete reset.',
  affirmation = 'I understand the levels of decontamination and where each one belongs. I carry this knowledge with authority because I earned it through study and understanding.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Sterilization';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'A hospital disinfectant is professional grade. It is formulated for environments where the stakes are high and the margin for error is small. When you use a hospital disinfectant on your tools, you are applying the same standard of care that medical professionals use. That is not a small thing. That is you saying my clients deserve the highest level of protection I can provide. Read the label. Follow the instructions. Respect the product and it will do its job.',
  affirmation = 'I use professional grade products because I hold myself to a professional grade standard. I read the labels. I follow the instructions. I trust the process.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Hospital Disinfectant';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Tuberculosis bacteria are among the hardest to destroy. If a disinfectant is labeled tuberculocidal, it means it has been proven effective against one of the toughest organisms out there. That is your benchmark. If it can handle tuberculosis bacteria, it can handle most of what you will encounter in a salon. Think of a tuberculocidal disinfectant as the heavy duty option, the one you reach for when you want to be absolutely certain your tools are safe.',
  affirmation = 'I choose strength when it matters. I understand what tuberculocidal means, and I know when to use it. My choices are informed, intentional, and protective.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Tuberculocidal Disinfectant';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'Universal precautions are not about assuming the worst about people. They are about holding yourself to the same standard every single time. You treat all blood and all bodily fluids as potentially infectious, not because you know they are, but because consistency is what keeps everyone safe. It is like putting on your seatbelt every time you get in a car, not just when the road looks dangerous. The professionals who protect themselves and their clients best are the ones who never take shortcuts.',
  affirmation = 'I do not pick and choose when to be careful. I am consistent. I am thorough. My universal precautions are not about fear. They are about integrity.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Universal Precautions';

-- Block 6: Safety Documents
UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'An exposure incident is the moment contact happens. Your skin, your eyes, your mouth, or your mucous membranes come into contact with blood or potentially infectious bodily fluids. It is not the time to freeze. It is the time to act. You have trained for this. You know the steps. Wash the area, report the incident, follow your protocol. The professionals who handle exposure incidents well are the ones who prepared before the moment ever arrived.',
  affirmation = 'I am prepared for the moments that matter most. I do not freeze. I do not panic. I respond with the training and knowledge I have built, and I trust myself to act.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Exposure Incident';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'A Safety Data Sheet is the truth about every chemical product in your salon. It tells you what is inside, what the hazards are, how to handle it safely, and what to do if something goes wrong. It is not paperwork. It is protection. Every product you use should have one, and you should know where to find it. The cosmetologist who reads the SDS is the one who never gets caught off guard. Knowledge is not just power in this case. It is safety.',
  affirmation = 'I read what others skip. I know what is in the products I use, and I know what to do if something goes wrong. My knowledge keeps me and my clients protected.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Safety Data Sheet';

UPDATE public.terms SET
  metaphor = 'The MSDS was the original version of what we now call the Safety Data Sheet. It served the same purpose, informing workers about chemical ingredients, hazards, and safety procedures. The newer SDS format is more standardized and consistent across industries, but the mission has always been the same. Know what you are working with. Understand the risks. Protect yourself. The name changed but the principle never did.',
  affirmation = 'I understand the evolution from MSDS to SDS. I carry the history and the current standard with equal respect. My commitment to chemical safety is unwavering.'
WHERE section_id = 'c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-ab3456789012' AND term = 'Material Safety Data Sheet';
